President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Joshua Gotbaum as Director of the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, Raul Perea-Henze as Assistant Secretary of Policy and Planning at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Carrie Hessler Radelet as Deputy Director of the United States Peace Corps, Eileen Chamberlain Donahoe as Representative of the United States Representative to the United Nations Human Rights Council, and Laura Kennedy as Representative of the United States to the Conference on Disarmament. Additionally, President Obama will appoint four individuals to serve on the Ronald Reagan Centennial Commission, including Peggy Noonan, John F. W. Rogers, Frederick J. Ryan Jr., and Fred W. Smith.